26/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- EU security chief Javier Solana and Iran's top nuclear negotiator, Ali Larijani, wrap up two days of talks in Ankara on Thursday (April 26th) focused on Iran's nuclear programme. After the first day of discussions, Solana told journalists that he hoped the negotiations continue and that issues are resolved via diplomatic means. Larijani noted some progress in certain areas, but he did not elaborate. The talks were scheduled in Ankara after Turkey offered to help facilitate dialogue between the EU and Iran. (Focus, Zaman - 26/04/07; AFP - 25/04/07)
